Sentencas: Dual-phase porous Ni-YSZ cermets were fabricated via the freeze casting of a ceramic/camphene slurry.
Titulo: Freeze casting of porous Ni-YSZ cermets

Sentencas: After removing the frozen camphene via sublimation at room temperature, the green samples were sintered for 3 h in air at various temperatures, ranging from 1100 to 1350 degrees C, and then reduced in an Ar-5% H-2 atmosphere at 700 degrees C for 3 h. The fabricated Ni-YSZ cermets showed 3-D pore channels formed by the replication of the entangled camphene dendrite network and small pores in the Ni-YSZ walls produced by partial sintering of the NiO-YSZ composite.
Titulo: Freeze casting of porous Ni-YSZ cermets

Sentencas: Furthermore, the fabricated samples were found to possess reasonable electrical conductivities, thus rendering them suitable for use as the basic components of planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Freeze casting of porous Ni-YSZ cermets
